.TH wxScreenDC 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxScreenDC \- A \fIwxScreenDC\fR can be used to paint on the screen.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This should normally be constructed as a temporary stack object; don't store a \fIwxScreenDC\fR object.

.PP
When using multiple monitors, \fIwxScreenDC\fR corresponds to the entire virtual screen composed of all of them. Notice that coordinates on \fIwxScreenDC\fR can be negative in this case, see \fIwxDisplay:getGeometry/1\fR for more.

.PP
